Ian Cockerill May Be Named CEO of Polyus Gold, Telegraph Says

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-02-27T13:41:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/ian-cockerill-may-be-named-polyus-gold-chief-telegraph-says.html
OAO Polyus Gold may name  Petmin Ltd .
Chairman Ian Cockerill to replace Mikhail Prokhorov as chief
executive officer, the  Sunday Telegraph  said, without saying
where it obtained the information.  Polyus has identified three international specialists in
gold mining as candidates for the job, the newspaper said,
citing an  interview  with Prokhorov, who has temporarily taken on
the role. Cockerill may be vying with  Randgold Resources Ltd .
Chief Executive Officer Mark Bristow for the post, the newspaper
said.  Anton Arens, a spokesman for Polyus in Moscow, declined to
comment when contacted by telephone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in London at 
